costly than we can imagine.

00:30:36.970 --> 00:30:39.429
And what's driving this?

00:30:39.429 --> 00:30:41.470
Well, what's driving the
fact that we are talking

00:30:41.470 --> 00:30:45.400
about climate change at all is
in fact what economists would

00:30:45.400 --> 00:30:49.120
call a free rider problem.

00:30:49.120 --> 00:30:51.460
It's not in anyone's
personal short term

00:30:51.460 --> 00:30:55.230
immediate economic interest to
do enough or for that matter,

00:30:55.230 --> 00:30:57.400
is it possible to do
enough as an individual

00:30:57.400 --> 00:31:00.340
to solve this problem
for the rest of us

00:31:00.340 --> 00:31:02.990
by decreasing CO2 emissions?

00:31:02.990 --> 00:31:05.906
If all of us here were or every
committed environmentalist

00:31:05.906 --> 00:31:07.530
on the planet decreased
their emissions

00:31:07.530 --> 00:31:10.630
to zero that would be laudable.

00:31:10.630 --> 00:31:12.740
That would be good.

00:31:12.740 --> 00:31:15.655
A, it probably wouldn't
even be possible.

00:31:15.655 --> 00:31:17.280
And I would even
question the statement

00:31:17.280 --> 00:31:20.004
whether it would
be good overall.

00:31:20.004 --> 00:31:21.420
Given current
technologists that's

00:31:21.420 --> 00:31:26.010
just not what we
could reasonably do.

00:31:28.570 --> 00:31:32.010
Well, turn this on its head.

00:31:32.010 --> 00:31:34.140
From the free rider
problem of it's

00:31:34.140 --> 00:31:36.250
not in any one
ours interest to do

00:31:36.250 --> 00:31:40.570
enough to what we call
the free driver problem.

00:31:40.570 --> 00:31:44.597
When you look at something like
the what techno fix, quick fix,

00:31:44.597 --> 00:31:45.430
like geoengineering.

00:31:49.070 --> 00:31:50.570
Dumping stuff into
the stratosphere

00:31:50.570 --> 00:31:55.720
to deflect sunlight and cooling
the planet while we are at it.

00:31:58.550 --> 00:32:03.370
Now, it turns out in
a very big crude form.

00:32:03.370 --> 00:32:05.320
we know that works.

00:32:05.320 --> 00:32:08.540
Volcanoes have been
doing it forever.

00:32:08.540 --> 00:32:13.110
At Mount Pinatubo,
Philippines, 1991,

00:32:13.110 --> 00:32:16.600
decreased global average
warming the following year

00:32:16.600 --> 00:32:19.580
by about 0.5 degrees
centigrade, which at the time

00:32:19.580 --> 00:32:21.660
was precisely the global
average warming up

00:32:21.660 --> 00:32:27.840
to that point since
pre-industrial times.

00:32:27.840 --> 00:32:28.340
It works.

00:32:31.000 --> 00:32:36.100
Now, first of all, I mean
one good way, frankly

00:32:36.100 --> 00:32:38.280
of describing what
geoengineering actually

00:32:38.280 --> 00:32:42.610
is, is it's basically
chemotherapy for the planet.

00:32:42.610 --> 00:32:45.600
So just because some
experimental drug

00:32:45.600 --> 00:32:47.950
worked on some rat
somewhere in a lab

00:32:47.950 --> 00:32:54.520
in not spreading cancer quite
as rapidly as it would have,

00:32:54.520 --> 00:32:59.700
doesn't mean you should
start smoking today.

00:32:59.700 --> 00:33:00.850
That's clearly not.

00:33:00.850 --> 00:33:06.110
Or like another analogy,
tracheotomy for the planet.

00:33:06.110 --> 00:33:08.110
So you probably
want to your doctor

00:33:08.110 --> 00:33:12.995
to have that in his back pocket
when you walk into the office.

00:33:12.995 --> 00:33:15.370
You probably don't want to
deal with a doctor who doesn't

00:33:15.370 --> 00:33:16.580
know what a tracheotomy is.

00:33:16.580 --> 00:33:17.914
Let's put it that way.

00:33:17.914 --> 00:33:20.080
Now, you certainly don't
walk into a doctor's office

00:33:20.080 --> 00:33:24.960
and say, sir, could you
please cut my throat open?

00:33:24.960 --> 00:33:26.590
I always wanted to
see what it's like.

00:33:29.200 --> 00:33:31.590
Clearly not.

00:33:31.590 --> 00:33:35.330
Now that's what I would
say is a pretty apt analogy

00:33:35.330 --> 00:33:38.950
