00:44:48.180 --> 00:44:49.910
So no, it's not zero.

00:44:49.910 --> 00:44:51.990
And yes, it will be the
ultimate catastrophe,

00:44:51.990 --> 00:44:54.114
swallowing up the universe
or the planet, at least,

00:44:54.114 --> 00:44:55.240
as we know it.

00:44:55.240 --> 00:45:00.410
On the other hand, when you look
at the chance of catastrophe

00:45:00.410 --> 00:45:04.820
where we say, well, it's at
least around 10% unless we act.

00:45:04.820 --> 00:45:10.360
In that case it is so much
lower that it's not zero

00:45:10.360 --> 00:45:13.571
but it might as well be.

00:45:13.571 --> 00:45:15.570
Or In other words, all
these other catastrophes,

00:45:15.570 --> 00:45:18.910
we look at nuclear catastrophe
and GMOs for that matter.

00:45:18.910 --> 00:45:21.760
GMOs is a fantastic
example too, by the way.

00:45:21.760 --> 00:45:26.640
So the public is scared.

00:45:26.640 --> 00:45:30.950
The average public is scared
of GMOs wreaking havoc.

00:45:30.950 --> 00:45:36.610
When you talk to the
well-informed scientist, most

00:45:36.610 --> 00:45:40.930
of them-- the vast,
vast majority of them--

00:45:40.930 --> 00:45:47.240
are much less worried about the
ultimate worst-case scenario

00:45:47.240 --> 00:45:51.470
when it comes to GMOs
than the general public.

00:45:51.470 --> 00:45:55.010
Flip gears and look at climate.

00:45:55.010 --> 00:45:57.590
The average climate
scientist is most

00:45:57.590 --> 00:45:59.510
definitely much,
much more worried

00:45:59.510 --> 00:46:03.430
than the average citizen.

00:46:03.430 --> 00:46:06.220
Not just here in
the US, everywhere.

00:46:06.220 --> 00:46:08.380
Europe, anywhere.

00:46:08.380 --> 00:46:12.930
And then what you actually
have is many of the more level

00:46:12.930 --> 00:46:16.280
headed climate scientists
have, in fact, moved on.

00:46:16.280 --> 00:46:18.470
And not moved on in sort
of worrying about GMOs,

00:46:18.470 --> 00:46:21.200
but moved on and
basically are now

00:46:21.200 --> 00:46:22.450
thinking about geoengineering.

00:46:25.720 --> 00:46:27.740
That's a real problem.

00:46:27.740 --> 00:46:30.620
So I'm not saying
climate change is unique.

00:46:30.620 --> 00:46:34.390
I would say it's unique in
the combination of these four

00:46:34.390 --> 00:46:37.176
long term, global,
irreversible, and uncertain.

00:46:37.176 --> 00:46:39.050
Which, of course, makes
it uniquely difficult

00:46:39.050 --> 00:46:43.050
to solve which is a
problem, a real problem.

00:46:43.050 --> 00:46:47.220
And more important
or equally important,

00:46:47.220 --> 00:46:49.990
it is probably the one
problem with the biggest

00:46:49.990 --> 00:46:57.755
gap between informed citizens
versus actual action.

