00:50:02.640 --> 00:50:04.514
have been going down,
because we're switching

00:50:04.514 --> 00:50:09.282
from coal to natural gas and
renewables in energy efficiency

00:50:09.282 --> 00:50:11.115
about a third, a third,
a third contributing

00:50:11.115 --> 00:50:15.260
here in the US and
lots of other factors.

00:50:15.260 --> 00:50:17.610
And of course,
right, I'm obligated

00:50:17.610 --> 00:50:23.450
to tell you that leveling
emissions isn't enough.

00:50:23.450 --> 00:50:26.550
Now we are filling the
bathtub at a steady rate.

00:50:26.550 --> 00:50:30.300
But we are still filling
the atmospheric bathtub.

00:50:30.300 --> 00:50:33.550
Which is, by the way, one
of these-- in many ways--

00:50:33.550 --> 00:50:37.990
very, very simple concepts
that when you, to be fair,

00:50:37.990 --> 00:50:39.800
not explain it with
a bathtub analogy

00:50:39.800 --> 00:50:42.240
but explain it in sort
of climate context,

00:50:42.240 --> 00:50:45.720
you quiz 200 above average
MIT graduate students.

00:50:45.720 --> 00:50:47.570
They get that wrong.

00:50:47.570 --> 00:50:51.660
They think that leveling
off emissions is the goal.

00:50:51.660 --> 00:50:53.160
When you think about
it as a bathtub

00:50:53.160 --> 00:50:55.390
it's pretty darn obvious
that that's not the case.

00:50:55.390 --> 00:51:00.510
Your bathtub will still
overflow if you have kept

00:51:00.510 --> 00:51:03.620
the inflow of water steady.

00:51:03.620 --> 00:51:08.610
What we have to do is
turn down the flow.

00:51:08.610 --> 00:51:11.700
Get to zero and even
below zero in order

00:51:11.700 --> 00:51:14.820
to stabilize global
average temperatures.

00:51:14.820 --> 00:51:17.950
So it's a heavy, heavy lift.

00:51:17.950 --> 00:51:21.510
That said, positive
examples-- well,

00:51:21.510 --> 00:51:28.450
we've seen the US China
climate deal last November.

00:51:28.450 --> 00:51:32.160
That in many ways no
one really expected.

